import java.text.SimpleDateFormat

import org.apache.spark.mllib.rdd.RDDFunctions._

import org.apache.spark.sql.functions.{collect_list, collect_set}

defined class LabResult

dateFormat: java.text.SimpleDateFormat = java.text.SimpleDateFormat@5069d960

paragraphs.text:
%spark2
// Create an RDD of Person objects from a text file, convert it to a Dataframe
val labDF = sc.textFile("/labdata/generated-data.csv").map(_.split(","))
  .map(attributes => LabResult(
      dateFormat.parse(attributes(0)).getTime() / 1000, 
      dateFormat.parse(attributes(1)).getTime() / 1000,
      dateFormat.parse(attributes(2)).getTime() / 1000,
      attributes(3),
      attributes(4).toDouble,
      attributes(5),
      dateFormat.parse(attributes(6)).getTime() / 1000,
      attributes(7)
      ))
  .toDF()

%spark2
import org.apache.spark.sql.expressions.Window
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._

val wSpec1 = Window.partitionBy("name").orderBy("obx_ts").rowsBetween(-5, 5)
val maDF = labDF.withColumn( "ma", avg(labDF("value") ).over(wSpec1)  )
maDF.filter($"name" === "chloride").registerTempTable("clma")
maDF.show()
%sql select row_number() OVER (order by obs_ts) as index, ma, value from clma
